  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add to a tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the potatoes are crisp – these are your <strong>roast potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1714473650884-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1714473650884-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1714473650884-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1714473650884-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1714473650884-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are in the oven, boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> roughly</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 50ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1714473656752-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1714473656752-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1714473656752-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1714473656752-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1714473656752-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grate your<strong> cheddar cheese</strong> into a bowl, add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>cheesy breadcrumb mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1714473673432-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1714473673432-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1714473673432-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1714473673432-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1714473673432-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your <strong>hake</strong> <strong>fillet[s] </strong>dry with kitchen paper and add them to a baking tray (or two!) (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>cheesy breadcrumb mix</strong> over the fish until totally covered</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min, or until the breadcrumb mixture is starting to turn golden and the fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>cheesy baked hake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1714473677998-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1714473677998-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1714473677998-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1714473677998-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1714473677998-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the hake is cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped</strong> <strong>red</strong> <strong>onion</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and<strong> tomato paste</strong> to the pan<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> and cook for 4-5 min further or until all the veg has fully softened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1714473791550-x200.jpg",
